Arshad Warsi and Maria Goretti share a beautiful relationship and will be celebrating their silver jubilee this Valentine&rsquo;s Day. Now, the Munna Bhai MBBS&nbsp;and Ishqiya actor has revealed in an interview with Bombay Times that they had not registered their marriage till now and did that recently on January 23!

In an interview with the publication, Warsi said, &ldquo;It crossed our minds, but we never thought that it was really important. But then we realised that it is important to do it when you have to deal with property matters and even after you are no more. We did it for the sake of the law. Otherwise, I feel as partners, if you are committed to each other, then that's all that matters.&rdquo;

In the same interview, the actor also revealed his reason for getting married on Valentine&rsquo;s Day. &ldquo;I hate to share my wedding date with anyone because it sounds so cheesy. Both Maria and I are embarrassed about this! It was never intentional though. Maria's parents wanted us to get married soon. We couldn't during Lent and then I was getting busy with work. We didn't want to waste one year and the one date that looked feasible to us back then was February 14, so we went ahead with it. Now I have the scariest memory of Valentine's Day &mdash; that I got married.&rdquo;

Warsi and Goretti met each other during a college festival in 1991 and were drawn to each other for their shared passion towards dance. The actor had gone there to judge a talent show and Goretti was a participant there. Later, the two became friends and she even joined Warsi&rsquo;s dance troupe. They dated for eight years before Goretti said &lsquo;I do&rsquo; to him in a traditional church ceremony on February 14, 1999, followed by a nikaah. Though their relationship hit a rough patch for a few months during the course of these 25 years, they managed to rise stronger as a couple. They have two children, son Zeke and daughter Zene.

Bigg Boss OTT, Season 2, winner Elvish Yadav is once more in the news. This time however, it is for a controversial video of him slapping a man. This incident was captured on video and was posted on social media earlier today.

YouTuber Elvish got into a fight at a restaurant in Jaipur. The video of the &lsquo;Bigg Boss OTT 2&rsquo; winner, that went viral, showed him slapping a stranger twice while he held out his hands in protest, and then storming out, but soon coming right back to engage with him again. At this point, his friends intervened and escorted him out.

Soon after the video that was posted on X went viral, Elvish Yadav released an audio statement claiming that the stranger had shouted obscenities and abuses at him and that is what led him to retaliate with a slap. He reiterated that he had no regrets about the incident.

The audio statement issued by him where he shared his perspective of the incident, he said, &ldquo;Bhai, dekho, matter ye hai, naa mujhe shauk hai ladai karne ka, naa mere ko haath uthane ka shauq hai. Main apne kaam se kaam rakhta hoon. Main chalta hoon normal. Aur jo photo khichwane ko kehta hai, hum kichwate hai aaram se photo. Par, jo koi piche se comment pass karta hai, usko nahi bakshte (I am not interested in fighting nor slapping someone. I click photos with whoever asks but if you make a personal remark, I don&rsquo;t spare them either).&rdquo;

Elvish added, &ldquo;As you can see, there were police and commandos with us. It is not that we&rsquo;ve done anything wrong. This was personal. He took a personal dig at me, and I went and slapped him. I don&rsquo;t have any regrets. Aisa hi hoon main (I am like this only). He hurled abuses and I reacted in my style.&rdquo;

At film promotions, seldom do you hear scribes probing about a film, on the contrary, they would rather pick on click-bait subjects that ensure traffic. And some actors prefer to throw caution to the winds and give them enough fodder for several Instagram reels. Tovino Thomas has in the past and very recently showed them who is the boss when it comes to dealing with the press.

At the promotions of&nbsp;Anweshippin&nbsp;Kandethum,&nbsp;when the writer Jinu Abraham was asked about the controversial scene in his previous film,&nbsp;Kaduva,&nbsp;and had to remove it owing to protests on social media, Tovino was quick to call out the journalist for the needlessly provocative question &mdash; &ldquo;You got your content, no? The writer owned up to his mistake too. Well done!&rdquo; he mocked the journalist.

At the same promotional event when he was asked if he would agree to do a politically incorrect role, he replied &mdash; &ldquo;If I play a villain, how do I make him politically correct? The problem is when you are glorifying such villains. If you had a fair idea of political correctness, you wouldn&rsquo;t be asking me this question.&rdquo;

During&nbsp;Minnal&nbsp;Murali's&nbsp;promotions, while agreeing that he wasn&rsquo;t articulate in English, he felt that wasn&rsquo;t a prerequisite to be an actor &mdash; &ldquo;I am not sitting here because I am an HOD of English literature in college.&rdquo;

At a press meet when he was asked about the current political climate in the state &mdash; &ldquo;I am not here to talk about politics. I have my politics and I don&rsquo;t think I need to share that with you. I haven&rsquo;t done any survey or homework regarding the current ruling party&rsquo;s chances in the next elections. Do you have any idea? Then how do you expect me to answer that?&rdquo;

Manjulika from Bhool Bhulaiyaa and Rooh Baba from Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2 are all set to meet &ndash; in Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3! Kartik Aaryan who played the character of Rooh Baba in 2022&rsquo;s blockbuster Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2 took to his Instagram to announce the third film in the franchise while also informing that he will be sharing screen space with Vidya Balan who will reprise her role from the original film. He posted a mash-up video of the two of them dancing to the popular Aami Je Tomaar number from their respective films and captioned it &lsquo;And its happening. Og Manjulika is coming back to the world of BhoolBhulaiyaa. Super thrilled to welcome&nbsp;@balanvidya&nbsp;This Diwali is going to be crackling.&rsquo;

Readers will recall that Balan starred in the first Bhool Bhulaiyaa film in 2007 alongside Akshay Kumar, Shiney Ahuja and Amisha Patel and directed by Priyadarshan. The psychological horror-comedy was an official remake of the Shobhana-starrer Malayalam film Manichitrathazhu&nbsp;(1993). The Hindi adaptation received positive feedback from critics and audience and went on to become the eighth highest grossing film of the year. Its sequel saw Tabu step into Balan&rsquo;s shoes and play twin sisters Anjulika and Manjulika. Aaryan played the fraud psychic Rooh Baba who tries to rid the haveli of the evil spirit Manjulika. Anees Bazmee directed the sequel, which also starred Kiara Advani. The movie went on to become one of the highest grossing films of that year, making it to the list of some of Aaryan&rsquo;s biggest hits.

Now that the third film in the franchise has been announced for a Diwali release, fans of the movies are thrilled that they will get to see Balan return as Manjulika, a character which seems to have become synonymous with her even though Tabu garnered a lot of appreciation for her performance in the sequel as well. It will be interesting to see who will win the battle between&nbsp;OG Manjulika and the clever Rooh Baba in Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3.

 In a major setback for Congress in Maharashtra ahead of the upcoming general elections, former chief minister Ashok Chavan resigned from the primary membership of the party on February 12. When asked about his next political move, the former CM said he would tell about it in 48 hours.

 As reports of his exit went viral, several Opposition leaders reacted to the development. Senior Congress leader Jairam Ramesh took to X (formerly twitter) and said, &amp;quot;When friends and allies leave a political party that has given them so much &mdash; perhaps even more than they deserved &mdash; there is some sadness. But for those who are beset by insecurities, that particular washing machine will always prove more attractive than ideological commitment or personal loyalty. What these betrayers do not realize is that their departure will open up massive new opportunities for those whose progress they have been hindering all along.&amp;quot;

 Congress Leader and LoP in the state assembly, Vijay Wadettiwar, expressed surprise at Ashok Chavan's resignation. He told ANI, &amp;quot;Ashok Chavan's resignation is shocking. The reason for the sudden resignation is not clear. He did not discuss it with me. I have worked with him for 16 years. He will explain the reason for his resignation. The way BJP is breaking the party (Congress)...voters will teach them a lesson.&amp;quot;

 Shiv Sena UBT leader Sanjay Raut, while reacting to Ashok Chavan's resignation, said, &ldquo;Ashok Chavan became a BJP member. I can&rsquo;t believe it. Till yesterday they were together... were discussing... gone today. Like Eknath Mindhe and Ajit Pawar, will Chavan also claim the Congress now and get a hand sign? And will the Election Commission give it to them? Anything can happen in our country!&rdquo;

 Chavan's exit comes days after other senior Congress party members &mdash; senior Maharashtra Congress leaders Milind Deora and Baba Siddique quit the party. Amid the rumours that Chavan may join the Bhartiya Janata Party (BJP), Maharashtra's deputy chief minister and member of BJP Davendra Fadnavis, told reporters &amp;quot;Aagey aagey dekho hota hai kya (wait and watch what happens further).&amp;quot;

India and the United Arab Emirates can collaborate on developing aerospace, artificial intelligence (AI), and education, among other sectors, Abdulnasser Jamal Alshaali, UAE ambassador to India said on February 12.

Commenting on MoU expectations between the two countries, he said, &ldquo;There are several MoUs that would be signed. The list has not been finalised yet because we're trying to do as many of them as possible&hellip;. In the last meeting, they discussed new sectors where the UAE and India could cooperate. Aerospace, for instance, AI, education, and so on.&rdquo;

The UAE&rsquo;s Ministry of Investment recently signed three Memorandums of Understanding (MoUs) with India. These agreements aim to expand bilateral investment cooperation in the renewable energy, food processing, and healthcare sectors.

Prime Minister Narendra Modi will be on a two-day visit to the United Arab Emirates beginning February 13, during which he is slated to hold wide-ranging talks with President Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan and inaugurate the first Hindu temple in Abu Dhabi. It would be the prime minister's seventh visit to the UAE since 2015, the Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) said. PM Modi and Al Nahyan will discuss ways to further deepen, expand and strengthen the strategic partnership between the countries and exchange views on regional and international issues of mutual interest.

With PM Modi's 2015 visit, a 34-year hiatus of an Indian PM to the UAE ended, and a new chapter in their relationship began. The relationship has since developed quickly, leading to the conclusion of three major agreements: a comprehensive strategic cooperation agreement in 2017, the Comprehensive Economic Cooperation Agreement (CEPA) in 2022, and the more recent Bilateral Investment Treaty (BIT) on February 1, 2024.

Reiterating the importance of PM Modi&rsquo;s visit to the UAE, the ambassador said: &ldquo;Such visits are very important in keeping the momentum in the relationship...This tells you how important the relationship is.... Cultural harmony is very important, it is a testament to acceptance, tolerance and co-existence. There is no other place like the UAE that could stand tall for its values when it comes to its values of acceptance of all ethnicities...&rdquo;

Commenting on India-UAE ties, Abdulnasser Jamal Alshaali said, &ldquo;The first visit (of the prime minister) was the turning point in the relationship. Although India-UAE ties date back several years, and the Indian diaspora have been here for quite some time, things were not happening at the pace that you see today -- thanks to the special bond and the special friendship between the two leaders.&rdquo;

The bilateral relationship between India and the UAE is strong, and trade ties between the two nations run deep. According to a press statement released by the Ministry of Commerce &amp;amp;amp; Industry on May 1, 2023, the UAE and Saudi Arabia are India&rsquo;s third and fourth largest trading partners. Also, the UAE is now the fourth-largest source of FDI for India, with a $ 3.5 billion investment.

City-based builder Arkade Developers will be investing around Rs 700 crore in three projects in the megapolis that are expected to be completed over the next three to four years.

Last week, the company received the regulatory nod to launch a Rs 430 crore initial share sale and part of the proceeds will be used for the investment.

&amp;quot;We have earmarked Rs 698 crore for three new projects in the city -- Arkade Nest in Mulund (West), Deep Shikhar C Unit in Goregaon (East) and Prachi in Vile Parle (East). &amp;quot;Phase 1 of Arkade Nest is a luxury project and is already on. Going forward, our focus is on blended model of greenfield and redevelopment. The Goregaon and Malad projects are redevelopment units,&amp;quot; Amit Jain, Chairman and Managing Director of Arkade, said &amp;quot;Phase 1 of Arkade Nest is a luxury project and is already on. Going forward, our focus is on blended model of greenfield and redevelopment. The Goregaon and Malad projects are redevelopment units.&amp;quot;

The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) in Mumbai on February 9 admitted an insolvency plea against Sporta Technologies Private Limited, the parent firm of fantasy sports major Dream11, over a rent default of Rs 7.6 crore.

The tribunal has appointed Madan Bajrang Lal Vaishnawa as the Interim Resolution Professional (IRP) responsible for handling the affairs of the company.

